# Frontend design lane

This repo uses the **Cursor Agent Stack frontend module**: Impeccable (direction + enforcement) + ui-ux-pro-max (lookup) + curated design references.

Apply when editing UI, CSS, or layout — not for API/backend-only changes.

## Before UI work

1. Read root **`PRODUCT.md`** (strategic) and **`DESIGN.md`** (visual tokens) when present.
2. If missing, run **`/impeccable init`** once — do not invent design context from scratch.
3. For `/impeccable` commands, follow `.cursor/skills/impeccable/SKILL.md` (run `context.mjs` once per session).
4. For inspiration, see **`.cursor/design-refs/README.md`** — pick **one** reference lane per task.

## Command shortcuts

| Intent | Command |
|--------|---------|
| First-time setup | `/impeccable init` |
| UX review | `/impeccable critique <surface>` |
| A11y / quality | `/impeccable audit <path>` |
| Typography pass | `/impeccable typeset` |
| Pre-ship cleanup | `/impeccable polish <target>` |
| Browser variants | `/impeccable live` (dev server + CSP setup) |

## Hooks (automatic)

- **Project**: Impeccable design detector on UI edits (`.cursor/hooks.json`).
- **Global**: secret-guard + session checkpoint from `~/.cursor/hooks.json` — stacks cleanly; do not duplicate checkpoint hooks in the repo.

## Stack pairing

| Tool | Role |
|------|------|
| **Impeccable** | Creative direction, 23 commands, 44 detector rules |
| **ui-ux-pro-max** | Palette/stack/UX lookup (Python CSV search) |
| **design-refs/** | Curated awesome-design-md links (not vendored YAML dumps) |

Preserve committed brand tokens in `DESIGN.md` unless `/impeccable typeset`, `/impeccable colorize`, or the user explicitly requests a redesign.
